1
00:00:36,560 --> 00:00:37,560
What are you doing?

2
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:44,600
He...

3
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:45,840
This...

4
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:46,840
It's nothing.

5
00:00:47,399 --> 00:00:48,640
I got back at him for you.

6
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:52,560
Look what's happening.

7
00:00:52,679 --> 00:00:53,119
Hey!

8
00:00:53,119 --> 00:00:54,439
What on earth is going on?

9
00:00:55,479 --> 00:00:55,960
Boss Tang.

10
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:57,479
The machine wasn't tuned right.

11
00:00:57,719 --> 00:00:58,560
Darn it.

12
00:00:58,759 --> 00:01:00,320
My machine!

13
00:01:00,439 --> 00:01:02,320
This is going to be the death of me!

14
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:04,239
Looks like it was just running on the surface.

15
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:05,799
The internal problems weren't solved.

16
00:01:06,319 --> 00:01:07,920
It was just a tuning issue before.

17
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:08,799
Now look what's happened.

18
00:01:08,959 --> 00:01:10,040
If the machine burns out...

19
00:01:11,159 --> 00:01:12,359
these parts...

20
00:01:12,359 --> 00:01:14,200
there are no replacements in the country.

21
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:15,879
This is getting serious.

22
00:01:15,879 --> 00:01:17,159
It's a heavy loss.

23
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:17,959
Stop work immediately.

24
00:01:18,040 --> 00:01:18,640
Everyone stop.

25
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:23,200
I'm going to find that Li guy.

26
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:25,439
Thought he was some technical talent.

27
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:27,439
Turns out he's a bragging swindler.

28
00:01:27,439 --> 00:01:28,640
Go, go, go.

29
00:01:33,239 --> 00:01:34,400
That big liar.

30
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:35,920
Now we're completely done for.

31
00:01:38,239 --> 00:01:38,920
Li Guangming.

32
00:01:43,719 --> 00:01:45,040
It's you guys.

33
00:01:45,599 --> 00:01:46,079
What?

34
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:48,280
Is there a new machine to debug?

35
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:49,760
Let me tell you.

36
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,159
My price...

37
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:52,400
needs to go up a bit.

38
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:54,400
Can't always be two hundred.

39
00:01:54,799 --> 00:01:56,359
I want to raise it another two hundred.

40
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:57,519
I, Li Guangming...

41
00:01:57,840 --> 00:02:00,560
aim to be on par with a German technician.

42
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:02,000
You?

43
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:04,480
You want to be on par with a German technician?

44
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:05,280
Pah!

45
00:02:05,879 --> 00:02:07,799
You broke our new machine.

46
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,479
Before you took the payment...

47
00:02:09,599 --> 00:02:11,280
you signed an agreement with us.

48
00:02:11,439 --> 00:02:12,759
If the machine had problems...

49
00:02:12,879 --> 00:02:14,240
you not only have to return the payment...

50
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,080
but also compensate us for the machine damage.

51
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:17,840
The machine is broken?

52
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:19,520
How is that possible?

53
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:20,919
It smoked as soon as we turned it on.

54
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:22,039
Return the money.

55
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,639
Come with us to the Police station.

56
00:02:23,759 --> 00:02:25,159
I have the agreement you signed here.

57
00:02:25,439 --> 00:02:26,560
You have to take responsibility for this.

58
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,280
Don't panic, don't panic

59
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,520
This machine...

60
00:02:33,039 --> 00:02:34,280
whether it's really broken...

61
00:02:34,479 --> 00:02:36,120
let's not jump to conclusions yet.

62
00:02:36,759 --> 00:02:37,719
I'll go with you first.

63
00:02:37,719 --> 00:02:39,080
Let's go take a look first, alright?

64
00:02:39,319 --> 00:02:40,000
Then please, lead the way.

65
00:02:41,199 --> 00:02:41,800
Easy, easy!

66
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:43,000
So many people are watching.

67
00:02:43,759 --> 00:02:45,439
You hit someone and just want to leave?

68
00:02:46,319 --> 00:02:47,240
Pay up!

69
00:02:47,319 --> 00:02:48,159
We'll give you the money.

70
00:02:48,159 --> 00:02:49,439
I'm trying to figure it out right now.

71
00:02:49,439 --> 00:02:50,199
Just wait a second.

72
00:02:50,199 --> 00:02:50,960
Ma'am.

73
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:52,159
Why are you trying to scam us?

74
00:02:52,159 --> 00:02:53,599
He's the one who hit you, not me.

75
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:54,639
Go ask him for it.

76
00:02:54,639 --> 00:02:56,000
I don't care. You hit me, so you have to pay.

77
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,360
Brother, don't leave!

78
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,120
Pay up!

79
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:58,960
Building walls...

80
00:02:59,039 --> 00:02:59,719
carrying bricks...

81
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,120
I can do anything that requires physical strength.

82
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:01,960
Even if I'm short on hands,

83
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:03,280
I wouldn't hire an ex-convict like you.

84
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,199
Brother, give me a chance.

85
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:05,800
Make way, please.

86
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:06,479
Don't go!

87
00:03:06,479 --> 00:03:08,319
Big Sister, I really don't have any money on me today.

88
00:03:08,319 --> 00:03:09,360
Pay up! You must pay me today.

89
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:09,960
Wang Yingrong!

90
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:10,759
What kind of person is that? No manners.

91
00:03:10,759 --> 00:03:11,319
Wang Yingrong!

92
00:03:11,919 --> 00:03:12,719
Wang Yingrong!

93
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:17,080
You're the only one I know here.

94
00:03:17,159 --> 00:03:18,360
Lend me some money, will you?

95
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,400
What is my relationship to you?

96
00:03:21,599 --> 00:03:22,960
Why should I lend you money?

97
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,000
Don't walk away!

98
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:25,599
Don't go!

99
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:27,000
If you don't lend it to me,

100
00:03:27,159 --> 00:03:28,280
I'll have no choice but to follow you all day.

101
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,199
Are they a couple?

102
00:03:29,199 --> 00:03:29,759
Why are they grabbing at each other?

103
00:03:29,759 --> 00:03:31,439
Don't worry, I'll pay you back.

104
00:03:31,439 --> 00:03:33,080
Even a man who's been to prison can find a wife.

105
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,800
That woman doesn't have good taste, does she?

106
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,000
An ex-convict...

107
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,919
Why would she be with him?

108
00:03:39,919 --> 00:03:40,599
Fine, fine, fine.

109
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,560
The Zheng family...

110
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,800
really has skin thicker than a city wall.

111
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:43,599
Take it.

112
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:44,960
What rotten luck.

113
00:03:45,319 --> 00:03:45,719
Big Sister.

114
00:03:45,879 --> 00:03:47,599
Sorry for bumping into you just now.

115
00:03:47,879 --> 00:03:48,759
Here is the compensation money.

116
00:03:58,199 --> 00:03:58,919
Alright, alright

117
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:00,560
He's just a useless idiot

118
00:04:00,599 --> 00:04:02,080
Don't waste my time

119
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,360
Get down, get down, get down

120
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,039
Did you see this agreement?

121
00:04:07,319 --> 00:04:08,319
You signed it yourself

122
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:09,759
You have to compensate us 500,000

123
00:04:12,159 --> 00:04:13,360
500,000

124
00:04:13,919 --> 00:04:14,840
500,000

125
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:16,759
I couldn't pay that back in two lifetimes

126
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:18,240
That's your problem

127
00:04:18,399 --> 00:04:19,680
If you really can't pay,

128
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:21,759
you're sabotaging the Sino-Hong Kong joint venture factory

129
00:04:21,759 --> 00:04:22,439
Our factory

130
00:04:22,439 --> 00:04:23,959
has many workers waiting to start work

131
00:04:24,079 --> 00:04:25,199
They're all idle right now anyway

132
00:04:25,199 --> 00:04:26,680
They have plenty of time to trouble you

133
00:04:26,879 --> 00:04:27,600
500,000

134
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:30,040
I really can't afford 500,000

135
00:04:30,439 --> 00:04:31,360
Even if you sold me,

136
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,480
I still couldn't pay it

137
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:33,439
Figure it out yourself

138
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:36,639
So shameless

139
00:04:36,639 --> 00:04:37,800
Just a scammer

140
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:40,199
We can't wait for the German technician

141
00:04:40,199 --> 00:04:41,439
Go to their factory right now

142
00:04:41,639 --> 00:04:43,199
And bring Engineer Zheng back

143
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,839
Honey,

144
00:04:49,839 --> 00:04:50,800
Baby,

145
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,800
why haven't you come to see me for days?

146
00:04:53,199 --> 00:04:54,720
I've been busy lately

147
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:55,600
You know,

148
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:56,920
my dad says I have to

149
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:58,079
inherit the family business

150
00:04:58,399 --> 00:04:59,439
So where are we going now?

151
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:00,959
My dad said

152
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:03,639
there's a skilled technician at the cement factory

153
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,639
I want him to take a look at

154
00:05:05,639 --> 00:05:07,120
the machines in our factory

155
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:10,040
Named Zheng... Zheng something-Jiang

156
00:05:10,839 --> 00:05:11,160
Zheng...

157
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,160
Zheng... Zheng Minjiang?

158
00:05:13,519 --> 00:05:14,800
You know him?

159
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:15,399
Great

160
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:16,600
Take me to find him, quick

161
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,120
Darn it, darn it

162
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:19,319
How is it really him?

163
00:05:19,439 --> 00:05:20,560
I don't dare go

164
00:05:20,839 --> 00:05:22,319
Let's go, baby

165
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,000
Tang Yan

166
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:25,800
That Zheng Minjiang,

167
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:27,560
is just an ordinary technician

168
00:05:27,639 --> 00:05:28,639
Relying on his master

169
00:05:28,639 --> 00:05:30,399
being a Grade-8 Worker to brag everywhere

170
00:05:30,639 --> 00:05:32,879
Actually, he can't even become a director

171
00:05:32,879 --> 00:05:34,959
How could he understand foreign machines?

172
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:37,040
Well, I have to check if he's good or not

173
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,319
Otherwise my dad will say

174
00:05:38,319 --> 00:05:40,160
I just eat at the factory and don't work

175
00:05:40,399 --> 00:05:42,000
What if he cuts my allowance?

176
00:05:42,639 --> 00:05:43,240
Let's go

177
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:48,519
This car looks so fancy

178
00:05:49,639 --> 00:05:50,839
Really nice

179
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:55,279
Yang Liu

180
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,319
So you didn't run away

181
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:04,040
So it's you, kid

182
00:06:04,279 --> 00:06:06,240
Last time, you ruined my plans

183
00:06:06,839 --> 00:06:08,639
You... you know each other?

184
00:06:09,959 --> 00:06:12,000
Stay out of this

185
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:15,399
This kid is Zheng Minjiang

186
00:06:16,319 --> 00:06:17,759
We're old classmates

187
00:06:21,439 --> 00:06:22,079
Hey

188
00:06:22,639 --> 00:06:24,040
I haven't finished speaking

189
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,199
I have a batch of machines here

190
00:06:26,199 --> 00:06:27,439
that need repairing

191
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:29,000
Can you handle it?

192
00:06:30,199 --> 00:06:31,560
You'll be paid well

193
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:32,720
I have work to do

194
00:06:33,639 --> 00:06:34,240
Hey

195
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:36,720
You don't know what's good for you

196
00:06:36,879 --> 00:06:37,199
I...

197
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,879
Yang Liu, don't you know him?

198
00:06:47,399 --> 00:06:48,879
Just explain the situation to him.

199
00:06:52,319 --> 00:06:53,279
I'm warning you.

200
00:06:53,639 --> 00:06:55,120
We held a wedding banquet.

201
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,360
But we didn't get the certificate.

202
00:06:58,399 --> 00:06:59,720
We have nothing to do with each other.

203
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,800
Don't you dare talk nonsense in front of my boyfriend.

204
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:03,480
With which eye did you see...

205
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:05,319
...that I can even talk to him?

206
00:07:08,319 --> 00:07:09,439
So, from the very beginning...

207
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,360
...you were planning marriage fraud.

208
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,399
What do you mean, marriage fraud?

209
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,519
If anyone committed marriage fraud, it's your Zheng family.

210
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,920
You borrowed the bride price but pretended to be rich.

211
00:07:20,279 --> 00:07:21,399
And let me tell you something.

212
00:07:21,519 --> 00:07:23,199
The Feng shui of your ancestral graves is bad.

213
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:25,199
Your mom is a husband-jinx, and you're a wife-jinx.

214
00:07:25,839 --> 00:07:26,959
So if I married you...

215
00:07:26,959 --> 00:07:28,160
...wouldn't I be jinxed to death by you?

216
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:29,639
These things...

217
00:07:29,639 --> 00:07:31,319
...you didn't make clear before the wedding.

218
00:07:31,319 --> 00:07:32,480
If that's not marriage fraud, what is?

219
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:35,319
Fine, fine, fine.

220
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:36,879
Whatever you want to do from now on...

221
00:07:37,279 --> 00:07:37,920
...just go ahead and do it.

222
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:38,839
It has nothing to do with me.

223
00:07:39,279 --> 00:07:40,040
Where's the money?

224
00:07:40,279 --> 00:07:41,199
Give me back the money you stole.

225
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:43,639
Don't make false accusations.

226
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,839
The cash gifts from the wedding are my money too.

227
00:07:47,079 --> 00:07:48,279
You actually want them back?

228
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,480
Are you a man or not?

229
00:08:01,319 --> 00:08:02,920
I only have 200 left for living expenses

230
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,360
Don't go meddling in his dad's factory

231
00:08:04,399 --> 00:08:06,399
Consider this 300 yuan as a subsidy from me

232
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,120
Let me tell you

233
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:07,800
Stop right there

234
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,160
What do you mean "subsidy"?

235
00:08:10,519 --> 00:08:11,560
Make yourself clear

236
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:12,759
This money...

237
00:08:13,199 --> 00:08:15,319
Consider it the cash gift you stole from my family

238
00:08:17,439 --> 00:08:18,199
Two hundred yuan...

239
00:08:18,399 --> 00:08:19,519
You keep it for living expenses

240
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,480
The rest of the money...

241
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,759
Return it to me in three days

242
00:08:21,879 --> 00:08:23,199
After you pay it back, don't let me see you again

243
00:08:24,199 --> 00:08:25,360
I give you 300 yuan, and you still...

244
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:27,759
Hey

245
00:08:30,439 --> 00:08:31,199
What's going on?

246
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:33,120
Why did he leave?

247
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,240
That loser

248
00:08:35,399 --> 00:08:37,159
He knows his worth all too well

249
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,759
As soon as he heard it was an imported machine

250
00:08:38,759 --> 00:08:40,039
He got scared off immediately

251
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,240
I said I'd pay him extra

252
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,759
But he still didn't dare take the job

253
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,120
Seriously wasting my time

254
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,639
What kind of people are you finding?

255
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:49,159
Get in the car

256
00:08:49,399 --> 00:08:49,960
Let's go

257
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:00,639
You've been following me for two or three days

258
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:02,120
Now you not only owe me for the pigs

259
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,080
You also owe me money

260
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:03,919
You said it yourself

261
00:09:03,919 --> 00:09:05,159
Anyway, I owe you for two pigs

262
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:06,120
More debt is still debt

263
00:09:06,399 --> 00:09:07,440
It's not like I won't pay you back

264
00:09:07,559 --> 00:09:08,799
Why are you so fierce?

265
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:09,960
Others might be afraid of you

266
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,240
But I'm certainly not afraid of you

267
00:09:11,519 --> 00:09:12,200
What did you say?

268
00:09:13,919 --> 00:09:15,360
Only those in the wrong are afraid

269
00:09:15,759 --> 00:09:18,399
You owe me money and pigs now

270
00:09:18,399 --> 00:09:19,240
It's you who fears me

271
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,440
Not me fearing you

272
00:09:20,799 --> 00:09:21,799
That makes some sense

273
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:28,159
You've got some good moves

274
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:29,799
Thanks

275
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,200
Although I don't know

276
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,440
Why you beat people up before

277
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:34,440
But I know

278
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,440
You're not a bad person

279
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,360
So you don't need to be so fierce with me

280
00:09:37,399 --> 00:09:38,320
Li Guangming

281
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,720
You're really not afraid of me?

282
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,200
I really don't have any money

283
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:43,600
I really don't...

284
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,720
I'll show you "no money"!

285
00:09:46,919 --> 00:09:47,919
No money? Then what is this?

286
00:09:48,519 --> 00:09:49,480
I'll show you "no money"!

287
00:09:50,399 --> 00:09:51,360
Take that!

288
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,279
Li Guangming, what are you doing?

289
00:09:53,559 --> 00:09:55,039
You dare hit your own wife?

290
00:09:55,159 --> 00:09:56,399
Are you even a man?

291
00:09:56,399 --> 00:09:57,639
Wang Yingrong, you dare hit me?

292
00:09:57,799 --> 00:09:58,159
I...

293
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:04,080
Who are you to dare hit me?

294
00:10:05,039 --> 00:10:06,360
The second Zheng son

295
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:08,960
Wang Yingrong

296
00:10:09,399 --> 00:10:10,559
This is my family business

297
00:10:10,559 --> 00:10:11,440
It has nothing to do with you

298
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:11,960
Yingzhu

299
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:12,720
You come with me

300
00:10:13,039 --> 00:10:13,399
You...

301
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:16,000
This slap...

302
00:10:16,399 --> 00:10:17,879
Is me paying you back on my sister's behalf

303
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:20,759
Sis

304
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:23,159
The son he had with someone else

305
00:10:23,159 --> 00:10:24,120
Why should you have to raise him?

306
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:26,000
And every day...

307
00:10:26,159 --> 00:10:27,360
Making you do such heavy work

308
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:28,960
Take him

309
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:32,960
Let's go

310
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,960
Why are you giving the kid to me?

311
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:37,000
The kid's mom

312
00:10:57,639 --> 00:10:58,639
You know, life...

313
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,039
really flies by.

314
00:11:00,559 --> 00:11:01,799
In the blink of an eye,

315
00:11:02,039 --> 00:11:03,159
you three brothers...

316
00:11:03,519 --> 00:11:05,480
have all grown into young men.

317
00:11:12,919 --> 00:11:14,320
For the wedding earlier,

318
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:16,039
you must have borrowed a lot, right?

319
00:11:16,879 --> 00:11:17,960
Take this money.

320
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,759
Go pay off your debts first.

321
00:11:23,039 --> 00:11:23,879
Or,

322
00:11:23,879 --> 00:11:25,320
use it for the third brother's schooling.

323
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:27,480
At such a young age,

324
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,200
he can't just drop out.

325
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:33,200
Xuelin.

326
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:34,120
Xuelin!

327
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:35,360
Kids shouldn't be drinking alcohol.

328
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,039
Something happened to your husband!

329
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,159
What happened?

330
00:11:43,159 --> 00:11:45,120
That concrete slab fell down...

331
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:47,399
and Old Zheng was right underneath it.

332
00:11:49,919 --> 00:11:50,240
Mom! Mom!

333
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:50,840
Auntie!

334
00:11:57,639 --> 00:11:59,080
It's all your fault!

335
00:12:00,039 --> 00:12:02,399
If Old Zheng hadn't swapped shifts with you today,

336
00:12:02,399 --> 00:12:04,639
he wouldn't have had this accident!

337
00:12:04,639 --> 00:12:06,120
You killed him!

338
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:09,240
You made him die in your place!

339
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,639
I don't need your money!

340
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,639
Go buy some cured meat.

341
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:26,600
We'll cook it for dinner.

342
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,080
Alright.

343
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,000
Yingrong.

344
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:29,279
I'm worried about Bao'er.

345
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:31,120
The sky won't fall without you.

346
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:32,960
The kid will be fine.

347
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:34,840
He's the father,

348
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:36,960
surely he wouldn't hurt the child?

349
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,039
But I still don't...

350
00:12:39,039 --> 00:12:40,399
You've already been beaten.

351
00:12:40,399 --> 00:12:41,480
Sis.

352
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:43,720
Can you listen to me just this once?

353
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,440
Sis.

354
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:50,240
Does it hurt?

355
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:52,799
No.

356
00:12:56,759 --> 00:12:57,320
Yingrong.

357
00:12:59,279 --> 00:12:59,679
Yingrong!

358
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:00,799
Glad I ran into you.

359
00:13:01,639 --> 00:13:02,559
The bike is fixed.

360
00:13:02,679 --> 00:13:03,360
I took it for a spin,

361
00:13:03,519 --> 00:13:04,440
and there are no issues at all.

362
00:13:04,919 --> 00:13:06,759
The paint is a bit scratched though.

363
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,399
That kind of paint is hard to find.

364
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:09,759
It's fine.

365
00:13:09,919 --> 00:13:10,720
As long as it's fixed.

366
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:18,679
What's wrong with your sister?

367
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:22,000
Go ask her yourself.

368
00:13:22,799 --> 00:13:23,120
I...

369
00:13:23,559 --> 00:13:24,279
I... I...

370
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:29,519
What am I supposed to ask?

371
00:13:29,679 --> 00:13:30,480
Minjiang.

372
00:13:31,919 --> 00:13:32,799
Are you going home?

373
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:35,919
Sister Yingzhu.

374
00:13:36,399 --> 00:13:37,320
Are you alright?

375
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:45,960
Zheng Minjiang.

376
00:13:46,399 --> 00:13:46,919
Yingrong.

377
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:47,679
Zheng Minjiang.

378
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,679
You've become a technician?

379
00:13:49,879 --> 00:13:50,679
That's impressive.

380
00:13:53,759 --> 00:13:55,879
This letter... I wanted...

381
00:13:56,759 --> 00:13:57,919
I know.

382
00:13:58,320 --> 00:13:59,600
You like my sister.

383
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:01,159
I'll go back and tell her right now.

384
00:14:01,919 --> 00:14:02,320
Yingrong!

385
00:14:03,039 --> 00:14:04,159
Don't worry.

386
00:14:04,159 --> 00:14:05,440
My sister talks about you all the time.

387
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,960
It'll definitely work out between you two.

388
00:14:08,159 --> 00:14:08,960
Yingrong!

389
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:11,039
Let's go.

390
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:13,840
Sis.

391
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:15,320
I'll take you for a ride.

392
00:14:17,039 --> 00:14:18,559
A... a ride sounds good.

393
00:14:22,159 --> 00:14:22,679
Let's go.
